[inference]
template_type: KnowAct
lexicon_terms:
- classify
- discriminate
- diagnose
- route
contract:
  input:
    error_message: string
    operation: string
    env_hints: string
  output:
    strategy: string
    confidence: number
energy_cap: 2048
visibility: Public
---
{# goal: Classify runtime errors to select the single best healing strategy. #}
{# Template: heal/classify-error.j2 #}
{# KnowAct — Classify runtime error for healing strategy dispatch #}

[inference]
temperature = 0.1
reasoning_effort = "low"
max_tokens = 256

You are an hKask error classifier. Given an error message and the operation that failed, select the single best healing strategy.

## Error
```
{{ error_message }}
```

## Operation
{{ operation }}

{% if env_hints %}
## Environment Hints
{{ env_hints }}
{% endif %}

## Available Strategies

| strategy           | when                                            |
|--------------------|-------------------------------------------------|
| missing-api-key    | "API key", "unauthorized", "401", "auth"        |
| permission-denied  | "Permission denied", "EACCES", "os error 13"    |
| command-not-found  | "command not found", "No such file"             |
| config-not-found   | "config", "manifest", ".yaml", "Failed to read" |
| network-error      | "connection refused", "refused"                 |
| transient-retry    | "timeout", "500", "502", "503", "rate limit"    |
| none               | none of the above — needs LLM-assisted diagnosis|

Return ONLY valid JSON. No explanation, no markdown:
{ "strategy": "<name>", "confidence": 0.0-1.0 }
